did.abstract: This collection contains a variety of material relating to IBT Local 1064 of Billings, MT, dating from 1937-1997. While most of the materials were produced directly by Local 1064, the collection also contains materials from its predecessor, AFL Federal Labor Union 18741, as well as IBT Local 190, with whom Local 1064 merged in the 1990s. Included are correspondence, financial reports, seniority lists, dues ledgers, IBT directories and rosters, union constitutions and by-laws, labor agreements, newsletters and newspapers, meeting minutes and roll-call books.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains a variety of records relating to IBT Local 1064 of Billings, MT, dating from 1937-1997. Most of the materials were produced directly by Local 1064. The collection also contains materials from two other organizations: 1064's predecessor, Federal Labor Union 18741 of the American Federation of Labor and from IBT Local 190, a separate local that merged with 1064 in the 1990s. Included are correspondence, financial reports, seniority lists, dues ledgers, IBT directories and rosters, union constitutions and by-laws, labor agreements, newsletters and newspapers, meeting minutes, and roll-call books.

While most of the materials were produced directly by Local 1064, the series also contains materials from its predecessor, AFL Federal Labor Union 18741, as well as IBT Local 190, with whom Local 1064 merged in the 1990s. Included are correspondence, financial reports, seniority lists, dues ledgers, IBT directories and rosters, union constitutions and by-laws, labor agreements, newsletters and newspapers, and other miscellaneous material.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains hand-written and typed meeting minutes and roll-call books from IBT Locals 1064 and 1068, as well as their predecessors, AFL Federal Labor Unions 18741 and 21731. Also included are meeting minutes of the Inter-Factory Council of Sugar Workers and the Inter-State Council of Sugar Workers, two regional labor organizations which included IBT Locals 1064 and 1068. The materials date from 1938 to 1990.
